                <!-- Accordion Item 3: Governance -->
                <div class="bg-white rounded-lg border border-slate-200">
                    <button class="accordion-header w-full flex justify-between items-center p-5 text-left text-lg font-semibold text-slate-800 hover:bg-slate-50">
                        <span><span class="text-blue-600">Pillar 3:</span> Governance & Content Relevance</span>
                        <span class="accordion-icon transform transition-transform">&#9662;</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="accordion-content">
                        <div class="p-5 pt-0 text-slate-600 space-y-4">
                           <p>A knowledge base is only as good as the trust users have in its content. We will implement rigorous governance to ensure information is always accurate, relevant, and easy to find. This prevents content decay and ensures high adoption.</p>
                           <ul class="space-y-3">
                                <li class="flex items-start"><span class="font-bold text-slate-700 w-32 shrink-0">Clear Ownership:</span><span>A designated team owns content strategy and quality.</span></li>
                                <li class="flex items-start"><span class="font-bold text-slate-700 w-32 shrink-0">Controlled Access:</span><span>Most users have read-only access to the main hub, with specific experts assigned editing rights to maintain integrity.</span></li>
                                <li class="flex items-start"><span class="font-bold text-slate-700 w-32 shrink-0">Feedback Loops:</span><span>Regular content audits and a clear channel for user feedback to request updates or new content.</span></li>
                                <li class="flex items-start"><span class="font-bold text-slate-700 w-32 shrink-0">Metadata > Folders:</span><span>Prioritize rich metadata tagging (by product, industry, use case) over deep folder structures for powerful, context-aware searching.</span></li>
                           </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
